name: PMQualityMode
desc: Constants that specify standard options for print quality.

items.name: var kPMQualityLowest: Int
items.desc: Specifies to use the lowest print quality available to the printer.

items.name: var kPMQualityInkSaver: Int
items.desc: Specifies to use a mode that saves ink, even if it slows printing.

items.name: var kPMQualityDraft: Int
items.desc: Specifies to print at the highest speed, with the amount of ink used as a secondary consideration.

items.name: var kPMQualityNormal: Int
items.desc: Specifies a general usage mode that balances quality and speed.

items.name: var kPMQualityPhoto: Int
items.desc: Specifies to optimize the quality of photos on the page, with speed not a concern.

items.name: var kPMQualityBest: Int
items.desc: Specifies to get the best print quality for all objects and photos on a page.

items.name: var kPMQualityHighest: Int
items.desc: Specifies to use the highest print quality available to the printer.
